About Jazwares Jazwares, a subsidiary of Alleghany Capital Corporation, specializes in consumer products including toys, plush, action figures, collectibles and musical instruments. Jazwares’ portfolio includes a variety of dynamic licensed and wholly owned brands. With over 20 years of design, development, and manufacturing experience, Jazwares is a company with a progressive focus on identifying new trends and transforming them into high-quality products for consumers of all ages. Jazwares, which is headquartered in Sunrise, FL, has offices around the world and sells in over 100 countries. Since its inception in 1997, Jazwares continues to grow through the development of new products and the strategic acquisitions of companies like First Act, Russ Berrie, Zag Toys, Wicked Cool Toys and Kellytoy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars CoComelon Deluxe Interactive JJ Doll: Not Just Another Toy, But a Playtime Companion
reviews.reviewText: If your little one is a fan of the popular CoComelon series, then the Deluxe Interactive JJ Doll is going to be an instant hit. This Amazon Exclusive doll is a multi-sensory toy that not only entertains but also helps in the developmental stages of preschoolers.First up, let's talk about the look. JJ comes dressed in a specially designed outfit featuring an adorable baby cow and baby chick on his shirt. He even comes with his own bowl of peas, spoon, and a cute pair of shoes. All theseaccessories give kids a lot to engage with, making the playtime experience rich and varied.Now, the interactive features are where JJ truly shines. Feed him the peas with the spoon, and you'll find them “disappearing” as if he’s really eating them. But it doesn't stop there. Press JJ's tummy and he'll reward you with laughter, fun phrases, and a selection of songs like "Yes Yes Vegetables," "This is the Way," and "My Name Song." These interactive elements make JJ not just another toy to stack in the corner, but an interactive buddy who can sing and talk back.Role-playing is key in a child’s developmental years. Kids can play dress-up with JJ, have feeding time, and even enjoy a little musical session. These play patterns not only keep a child entertained but also stimulate their imagination and cognitive skills.Another perk? If your kiddo loves all things CoComelon, there's more merchandise to collect. Plush toys, figures, and other CoComelon-themed items can join JJ in your home to create a full-fledged CoComelon universe.To sum it up, the CoComelon Deluxe Interactive JJ Doll offers a well-rounded play experience thattaps into a child's imagination, auditory senses, and fine motor skills. Whether it’s the delightful costume, interactive features, or the scope for imaginative play, JJ scores on all fronts. So, if you're looking to add a splash of educational fun to your child’s toy collection, JJ might just be your answer.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My daughter loves it!
reviews.reviewText: My daughter is eight years old with learning and coordination issues and she loves JJ. So when I saw this during black Friday sales I ordered it. This wasn't the only JJ she received for Christmas but to our surprise this is the one she's been playing with continuously for the past hour. As other reviewers have said, it does take some coordination to load the spoon with peas and a bit more to get JJ to eat them. My daughter is stubborn and keeps on trying until the peas disappear though. For this reason it may prove a little too challenging for younger kids. I'm still giving a five-star review simply because my daughter loves it so much!

There is no way that the JJ doll I received is a fake. It comes in frustration free packaging, so no, it is not packaged the same way as Walmart's doll. The shirt is not the same as the Walmart doll but it is a shirt that JJ wears in the Cocomelon videos.If this is a fake, it's an extremely good one. JJ says lots of phrases and sings a couple of songs. The volume is not adjustable but as far as toy volumes go, this one is pretty reasonable. It's not loud enough for the sound to be distorted, but it is still loud enough for a kid to play with while watching Cocomelon and be able to hear what JJ says.The peas and spoon... It's awesome, but like many brand new toys the mechanisms are stiff. It's hard to use because it has to hit JJs mouth perfectly for the peas to snap back into the spoon. My 2.5 year old didn't mind at all, she still thought it was great, and when she couldn't get JJs mouth to make the peas snap back, she resorted to smacking the spoon across JJs face to make the peas disappear. Aggressive, but crafty.She was so excited about JJ she didn't open any Christmas presents after him because he was IT. Now he goes everywhere with her.I would 100% recommend this doll for any cocomelon fan.
